<dl id="n06155h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06155h">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06155h"> 155(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">+</font> made a curse for us <small>Red</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n06155h"><li>FW 62.17 </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/lexc.htm#n06155h">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/c/l39c.htm#n06155h">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n06155h">MS BL 47471b-10v</ms> </li><li>JJA 45:151 <a name="c20d" href="../../ff/fdra/cda.htm#c20d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/c/c20d.htm#n06155h">Draft: I.3&sect;2.0</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">By reason of indwelling sin man is unable to render the obedience required by God&apos;s law, &ldquo;For all have sinned and come short of the glory of God.&rdquo; The sentence pronounced by the law upon the transgressor is death; but Christ by His obedience to the law has wrought out a deliverance from the curse of the law: &ldquo;<mark>Christ hath redeemed us from the curse of the law, being made a curse for us</mark>.&rdquo; <small> Anonymous, <a name="ATCC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ATCC"><cite title="source">Analysis of the Church Catechism</cite></a> (1879) 33</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
